text: Thirty yards from shore, three black swans were gliding over the water, so serene … no one had told them that war had come, and they cared nothing for burning towns and butchered men. She stared at them with yearning. Part of her wanted to be a swan. The other part wanted to eat one.
source: Arya Stark, A Clash of Kings

summary: as promised, here are some photos of our cosplays from the weekend - featuring sansa, margaery, and arya!  we all got stopped so...
caption:
as promised, here are some photos of our cosplays from the weekend - featuring sansa, margaery, and arya! 

we all got stopped so many times for photos and compliments (there was even a guy who could barely speak because of a sore throat but made sure to come over and say how much he loved our costumes - honestly, what a sweetheart!) there weren’t many game of thrones cosplays so people appreciated our efforts! i would walk down the corridors and here people say variations of: “that’s sansa stark!”, “she’s the lady of winterfell!”, “lady stark (bows)”, “my queen!” and i wanted to die of happiness!

also thoughts and feelings: should i upload the last picture and tag sophie on twitter in the hopes the feeling is mutual when it comes to “leaks” of sansa’s death in s8??

summary: Sansa elbowing Arya once Gendry inevitably stumbles half dead into Winterfell and giving her the eyebrow because all of a sudden...
body:
Sansa elbowing Arya once Gendry inevitably stumbles half dead into Winterfell and giving her the eyebrow because all of a sudden Arya isn’t anything like the sister Sansa remembered or is meeting for the first time.

Arya’s eyes go wide, her skin suddenly goes pale, and her breathing stills, it worries Sansa because that combination heralds trouble. Then her cheeks begin to redden and she blinks, swearing under her breath, and muttering about acorns.

It’s the most unusual moment Sansa has experienced in a long while because it almost feels as though they hadn’t been so badly broken. She was going to get to mercilessly tease her sister, and know that while Arya is deadly, as her older sister she’s immune.

summary: Soft Shit you think J/D should talk about in season 8
body:
Soft Shit you think J/D should talk about in season 8

Dany: Viserys and growing up homeless with no family but him. RHAEGO (and the loss that she still feels) and how the dragons work into that. The unburnt. Hatred of slavery/desire to make the world a better place


Jon: being the blight on Ned Stark’s honor. Never knowing who his mother was (and Catelyn Stark’s effect on him). ARYA. ROBB. Why he left Winterfell (it’s never really felt like a home to him). AEMON.

Dany: Viserys and growing up homeless with no family but him. RHAEGO (and the loss that she still feels) and how the dragons work into that. The unburnt. Hatred of slavery/desire to make the world a better place


Jon: being the blight on Ned Stark’s honor. Never knowing who his mother was (and Catelyn Stark’s effect on him). ARYA. ROBB. Why he left Winterfell (it’s never really felt like a home to him). AEMON.

title: 6SS - Sansa & Arya - Reunion
body:
Their reunion was quiet and full of calm for two people that had a lot to say to each other.

There was no reclamation, no demands, no screams, nothing, just calm and a warm embrace. The tears that fell were silent.

They both knew that they had a lot to say, they had parted in such a horrid way that it tore at both of them, they were family and they loved each other.

Their voices were quiet, full of grief and full of emotions, apologizing to one another for mistakes that happened, for the cruel things said, for actions taken and those that were not.

Life had been cruel to them, separating each other when they needed each other the most.

But now they were together, they were sisters who loved one another and nothing would ever tear them apart again.
